   4. Region & Zone (Very Important) : [Choose region close to application]
   -----------------------------------
      Region : Where DB physically lives [Ex : asia-south1] 
      Zone options:
         Single Zone
         High Availability (Multi-zone)
      Single Zone
        âœ” Cheaper
        âŒ No automatic failover : No automatic failover means if the database instance goes down, it will not switch to another instance automatically and requires manual intervention to restore service.
      High Availability (Recommended)
        âœ” Automatic failover
        âœ” Zero manual intervention
        âŒ Slightly more cost
     ğŸ‘‰ Interview line:
           Production workloads should use HA configuration.

    5. Machine Configuration (CPU & Memory) : 
    ------------------------------------------
         Choose:
           Shared core (small workloads)
           Dedicated core (production)
        If you choose less:
          âŒ Slow queries
          âŒ Connection issues
        If you choose more:
          âŒ Higher cost
        ğŸ‘‰ You can scale vertically later, but brief downtime may occur.

   6. Storage Configuration (Critical) :
   -------------------------------------
        > Storage Type : 
        ----------------
          SSD (recommended) : SSD is recommended because it provides much faster read/write performance and lower latency,
          HDD (cheap, slow) : HDD is cheaper but significantly slower, which can impact database performance
       ğŸ‘‰ Always choose SSD for production
        > Storage Size : 
        ----------------
           Example : 100 GB, If too small:  âŒ DB stops when disk is full
        > Enable Automatic Storage Increase :
        -------------------------------------
           What it does :
             GCP automatically increases disk when itâ€™s almost full
           If ENABLED:
              âœ” Prevents outages
              âœ” Safer for production
          If NOT enabled:
            âŒ Disk full â†’ DB becomes read-only
            âŒ Manual intervention required

   7. Connectivity Options :
   -------------------------
        > Public IP : [NOT best practice]
        -------------
            Cloud SQL gets a public IP and accepts connections from the internet, restricted by IP allowlist and encrypted using SSL.
            Needs:
              Authorized networks (IP allowlist)
              SSL
              âœ” Easy to connect
              âŒ Less secure
            Why NOT best practice: Exposed to the internet, higher attack surface, relies heavily on firewall rules.
        > Private IP (Recommended) :
        ----------------------------
            DB gets private IP inside VPC [Cloud SQL is assigned a private IP inside your VPC using Private Service Access, and traffic flows entirely over Googleâ€™s internal network.]
            Requires Private Service Access
              âœ” Secure    
              âœ” Low latency
             âŒ Slight setup complexity
          Private IP is preferred for internal applications.
          Why best practice: No internet exposure, lower latency, stronger network isolation for internal applications.
        > Cloud SQL Auth Proxy / Connector :
        ------------------------------------
            IAM-based secure connection [The proxy authenticates using IAM, creates a secure tunnel to Cloud SQL, and forwards traffic without exposing DB credentials or IPs. ]
            No DB passwords exposed
               âœ” Best practice
               âœ” Highly secure 
            Why best practice: Eliminates password management, avoids public IPs, works seamlessly with IAM and private networking.

   8. Backup & Recovery Options :
   ------------------------------
       > Automated Backups :
       ---------------------
         Choose:
           Enable
           Backup time window
         If ENABLED:
           âœ” Disaster recovery
           âœ” Point-in-time recovery
         If DISABLED:
           âŒ No recovery if data is lost
        ğŸ‘‰ Always enable backups
       > Point-in-Time Recovery (PITR) :
       ---------------------------------
         Uses binary logs / WAL logs
         Restore DB to specific timestamp
         âœ” Excellent for accidental deletes 

   9. Maintenance Options :
   ------------------------
       Maintenance Window
         Choose day & time
         GCP applies updates here
       If NOT specified:
         âŒ Updates can happen anytime
         ğŸ‘‰ Set maintenance window during low traffic

   10. Advanced Options (Interview Gold â­)
